<!DOCTYPE recipe [<!ELEMENT recipe ((title?,details?,ingredients, instructions?,cuisine) | (title?,cuisine,details?,ingredients, instructions?))><!ELEMENT title (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT cuisine (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT ingredients (ingredient*)><!ELEMENT ingredient (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT instructions (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT details (#PCDATA)><!ATTLIST ingredient amount CDATA #REQUIRED>]>
<recipe>
<title>
Cake Batter Rice Krispies Treats
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 5 minutes
COOK TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 15 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
SERVINGS: 20 pieces
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="6.0 Cup">Krispie</ingredient><ingredient amount="6.0 Tablespoon">Butter</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Melt butter in a large, heavy pot over low heat.
Add marshmallows. Stir until marshmallows are almost melted.
Remove from heat.
Add the cake mix, and stir to combine.
Stir in cereal.
Fold in half sprinkles, if using.
Press into greased 13x9-inch dish, and top with remaining half sprinkles, if using.
Gently press sprinkles into the top, and let treats set up.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>